 <p>" No matter how subtle the wizard, a knife between the shoulder blades will seriously cramp his style"  -- Vlad Taltos</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usterk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sterk</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/4/01 12:31:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=174.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Accept the duel</span><hr size=1> --A rogue should NEVER be the challenger...always accept it, and only do so when ready to do the two following things:<br>
<br>
1) Pumice the bastard--removes whatever their first buff is (if they're smart, they'll have a junk buff up first--if not, you'll be getting rid of SoW or a Damage Shield...good for you!)<br>
<br>
2) Land a Backstab and Poison at the same time<br>
<br>
Easy, eh?<br>
<br>
Basically, for duels--I tick someone off until they challenge me...once they do I find them, hide, apply a poison (blind or system shock or snare, depending on class)and get ready to accept.  Then I watch them...usually casters will med if they think you're not ready yet...so get behind him, accept the duel and backstab/poison.<br>
<br>
If a melee type, they'll wonder where you are--just get behind them and do the same as with casters.<br>
<br>
You're already way ahead.<br>
<br>
Now stay out of range of the charging melee's attacks (or stay near a caster to interrupt spells and go nuts.<br>
<br>
Good luck and good hunting to you.<br>
<br>
-Sterk Shadowhunter<br>
